Judy Heumann was a trailblazer and advocate for disability rights in America. She dedicated her life to fighting for the dignity of people with disabilities, resulting in landmark achievements such as the Rehabilitation Act, Individuals with Disabilities Education Act, and the Americans with Disabilities Act. Judy served in leadership positions in two presidential administrations and started multiple disability advocacy organizations. She was known for her courage and fierce advocacy. Former Vice President Joe Biden, who knew Judy personally, hosted a meeting with her at the White House to discuss efforts to break down barriers for those facing discrimination and neglect. Judy's legacy is an inspiration to all Americans, including those in the current administration. Joe and Jill Biden send their condolences to Judy's husband and family.